.row.featurette
  .col-sm-7.col-md-7
    %h2 Making the Distribution Smaller and Faster
    %p
      An Atomic Controller is a slimmed-down system designed to run Docker 
      containers, built from upstream CentOS, Fedora, or Red Hat Enterprise 
      Linux RPMs. It provides the benefits of the original distribution, plus 
      the ability to perform atomic upgrades and rollbacks &mdash; giving the best 
      of both worlds: A modern update model from a Linux distribution you know 
      and trust.

    %p 
