.row.featurette
  .col-sm-5.col-md-5
    %img.img-responsive{:alt => "Generic placeholder image", "src" => "http://place-hoff.com/325/150"}/
  .col-sm-7.col-md-7
    %h2 Enforcing Strict Security for Containers
    %p
      Atomic Controllers use SELinux to confine Docker containers with strong 
      mandatory access control to provide multi-tenant Docker systems with strong 
      security.

    %p 
      This will be a chapter that ties all this to SELinux and the rest.

.row.featurette
  .col-sm-7.col-md-7
    %h2 A Cockpit View of the Containers and OS
    %p
      Cockpit enables administration of Linux servers via a Web browser, letting 
      admins manage storage, services, and inspect journals straight from the browser 
      &mdash; but it doesn't preclude using other management tools or doing it straight 
      from the terminal. Cockpit has been extended to help you manage containers as well, 
      giving you full control over your IT resources.

    %p 
